 AI Assisted UI Hackathon Challenge
 Task: Build a School Website (Browser-Based)

Objective:-

Design and develop a simple, clean, and user-friendly School Website using HTML and CSS only, which runs locally in a web browser (no hosting or deployment required).

The goal is to test:

Basic web development skills
UI design sense
Logical structuring of content
 Functional Requirements

Students must create a website with the following minimum sections/pages:

 1. Home Page (index.html)
School name/logo
Welcome message
Banner or heading section
Navigation menu linking to other sections/pages

 2. About Section
Vision and Mission
Brief history of the school
Achievements (optional)

 3. Academics Section
List of subjects (Science, Commerce, Arts, etc.)
Facilities (Library, Lab, Sports, etc.)

4. Staff Section
List of teachers
Roles (Principal, Teachers, Staff)

5. Notices Section
School announcements
Events
Exam schedules

6. Contact Section
Phone number
Email address
School address
(Optional) Simple contact form

7. Footer (Common in all pages)

Website must run by simply opening:
 index.html in browser
 Suggested Folder Structure
school-website/
│
├── index.html
├── about.html
├── academics.html
├── staff.html
├── notices.html
├── contact.html
│
├── css/
│   └── style.css
│
├── images/
│   └── (all images here)
 

Students should ensure:

Clean layout (no clutter)
Proper alignment and spacing
Consistent colors and fonts
Readable text
Easy navigation
Creativity Freedom

Students are encouraged to:

Add images and icons
Use different color themes
Add hover effects (CSS)
Try simple animations (optional)
Time Duration
Total Time: 45 Min to 1 hr

 Evaluation Criteria:-

 Design & Creativity	
 Structure & Layout	
 Navigation & Usability	
 Functionality	
 Code Organization	


Students must submit:-

Complete project folder
Must include:
All .html files
style.css
Images (if used)
The project should open correctly in browser using:
> index.html
> Rules
> No internet required
> No frameworks (Bootstrap, Tailwind, etc.)
> No copying from others
> Work individually or in teams (based on your rule)
